<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PersonNote/1> rdfs:label "Person Note: #1" ;
	a dprr:PersonNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cicero's mention of the son of Acidinus in connection with the style of living that the younger Calpurnius Bibulus, Valerius Messalla Corvinus, and the son of Cicero himself could keep up in Athens in 45 (Cic. Att. 12.32.2; cf. Fam. 4.12.2) suggests that his rank was comparable to that of their fathers. (TJC)" .
